# No API keys are required for v1 — every data source in the default config is free
# and keyless (NOAA CO-OPS, NOAA NDBC, NWS api.weather.gov, Open-Meteo).
#
# Optional: richer swell data from Stormglass.io (documented marine API,
# ~10 requests/day on the free, non-commercial tier). Leave unset to disable.
# STORMGLASS_API_KEY=

# Optional: HERE Traffic API v7 key for the per-town "ramp & marina traffic score"
# (https://platform.here.com — free tier available). Leave unset to disable;
# the Ramp & marina traffic card degrades to "—" and the rest of the page renders
# normally. Set this as a HOST project env var (Netlify/Vercel), NOT a GitHub
# Actions secret — the Next app fetches HERE live, server-side; no Action calls it.
# HERE_API_KEY=

# Some upstreams (notably api.weather.gov) ask for a descriptive User-Agent with
# contact info. Customize it for your deployment.
CONDITIONS_USER_AGENT="isitboatday (contact: you@example.com)"

# Optional: override where the precomputed GOES GLM lightning feed is read from.
# Defaults to the shared lightning-data branch in the jayfrid-bot/bocabeach repo
# (kept as the GLM upstream through the boat-day pivot). Point this at your own
# branch/URL if you relocate the feed.
# LIGHTNING_FEED_URL=
